[{'comment_id': 905166418, 'comment_body': 'rename:
do_pgr_hawickCircuits  -> do_hawickCircuits

One of the things I am doing for v4.0 is to remove the unnecessary prefixes/suffixes from files & functions

That `do_pgr_foo` is inhertitance of 2.0

Please do that adjustment.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 23, 15, 26, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 905170138, 'comment_body': 'As mentioned on the stream, to avoid name clashing on the doxygen, remove the names on the header, you can "keep" the name as a comment, as in this example:

`Edge_t  *data_edges,`   ->  `Edge_t  *,   //  data_edges`

Do the same on the rest of the parameters of the header', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 23, 15, 30, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 905178803, 'comment_body': 'This comment is also an inheritance of 2.0.
Please remove.
It is annoying that if you change the sql file, then you have to look for all the comments to fix this.
It is better not to have it.
In any case if you modify the SQL, the compiler will let you know what needs to be changed.

If you really need that reminder of how the SQL looks like, then while developing, you could have a link to:
https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/blob/nitish-2022/sql/circuits/_hawickCircuits.sql
but if you do, open an issue in your fork to remind you that this link has to be deleted before merging to pgRouting.

', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 23, 15, 37, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 905181055, 'comment_body': 'Just for security reasons

It is better not to have it.
